:: Guard_Report_Portuguese {"position":"800,1000","size":"100,100"}
“Hang Dayang, an urgent summons. Foreign envoys seek an audience and there are whispers of Portuguese ships near the strait.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_Change_Begins")
]


:: Guard_Summons_Entry {"position":"900,1000","size":"100,100"}
A knock sounds at the door and a palace guard bows deeply.
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Guard_Report_Portuguese")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Arrival {"position":"1200,300","size":"100,100"}
A woman in elegant but practical attire approaches, scrolls tucked beneath one arm, a keris she does not flaunt at her waist.
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_Greeting")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Change_Begins {"position":"700,1000","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang grows serious as tension settles in the room. “It begins earlier than I feared.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "P_Asks_Begins")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Change_Warning {"position":"800,1100","size":"100,100"}
“Change. And change rarely arrives with gentle footsteps.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Courtyard_Night_Arrival")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Control_Not_Trade {"position":"1300,1300","size":"100,100"}
“But these men seek control, not exchange.”

(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_Remembered")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Disciplinary_Duty {"position":"1000,1600","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang’s tone grows disciplined and resolute. “If our city falls one day, the palaces may burn and the rulers may scatter, but the story must live.”

(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_Save_Truth")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Duty_Memory {"position":"900,800","size":"100,100"}
“As a scribe, observe everything. Our duty is not to the moment, but to memory.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_Question_Motivation")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Golden_Age {"position":"1300,400","size":"100,100"}
“You will write of this golden age, but remember that a golden age is not simply prosperity. It is discipline. It is protocol.”
click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_Sejarah")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Greeting {"position":"1300,300","size":"100,100"}
“You must be the one summoned from the outer districts. I am Hang Dayang, court scribe to His Highness. Walk with me.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "P_Response_Respect")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_History_Moves {"position":"1200,1400","size":"100,100"}
She gestures toward the hall. “Come. History is moving tonight.”

(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Riverside_Midnight")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Ming_Respect {"position":"700,800","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang watches the river, thoughtful. “The Ming recognized Melaka as a vassal not out of weakness, but out of respect. Their envoys strengthened our legitimacy.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Scribes_Quarters_Night")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Not_Bow {"position":"900,1300","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang turns, calm but alert. “Melaka was never built to bow.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Dang_Jelita_Cannons")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Past_Powers {"position":"1100,1300","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang steps forward with a firm gaze. “Others came before them, Arabs and Indians and even the great fleets of China. None claimed our waters as their own.”

(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Courtyard_Quiet_Wind")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Question_Motivation {"position":"1000,800","size":"100,100"}
She places a blank scroll in your hands. “Tell me. Why did you join the court?”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Scribe_Choice_Hub")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Remembered {"position":"1300,1400","size":"100,100"}
She looks toward you with steady intent. “The court must hear this, and it must be remembered.”

(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_History_Moves")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Save_Truth {"position":"1100,1600","size":"100,100"}
She places a hand on your shoulder. “You are a scribe. If you cannot save the throne, save the truth.”

(click:?page)[
    (goto: "P_Thought_Chill")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Sejarah {"position":"1200,400","size":"100,100"}
“Have you read the Sejarah Melayu?”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "P_Sejarah_Reply")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Sumptuary_Laws {"position":"1000,400","size":"100,100"}
“Then you know the rules. Yellow garments are only for royalty and gold-threaded fabrics are forbidden to common folk unless permitted. Sumptuary laws guard order as surely as the city walls.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Dang_Jelita_Entrance")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Wisdom {"position":"1500,300","size":"100,100"}
“The honour is in recording truth with clarity. Words survive longer than palaces.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Market_Bazaar_Evening")
]


:: Hang_Dayang_Worried_Storm {"position":"900,1600","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang’s voice is quiet and troubled. “Melaka has survived storms, but this one feels different.”

(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Hang_Dayang_Disciplinary_Duty")
]


:: History {"position":"1200,1000","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang pauses for a moment. “A dangerous curiosity, but perhaps necessary. History does not wait for those who fear it.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Guard_Summons_Entry")
]


:: Hornbill_Intro {"position":"1000,300","size":"100,100"}
“So this is Melaka… a city where eighty-four languages are said to mingle. A place the world flows through.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Protagonist_Intro")
]


:: Lively {"position":"1400,700","size":"100,100"}
Dang Jelita’s tone returns to normal. “Lively? This is a quiet day. Wait until the monsoon winds change. Ships will arrive like migrating birds.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Post_Choice_Return")
]


:: Loyalty {"position":"1100,1000","size":"100,100"}
Hang Dayang speaks steadily. “Loyalty is a virtue, but loyalty must stand on knowledge.”
(click:?page)[
    (goto: "Guard_Summons_Entry")
]


